Revitalizing Conflict-Affected Enterprises

Addis Ababa Job Creation Bureau

Transformational Leadership Training

11 sub-city sector heads and 155 high-level experts were trained on Transformational Enterprise Leadership and Entrepreneurial Mindset in Adama and Debrezeit cities.

Key Achievements:

  • Customized training modules developed for public experts

Our Approach

Comprehensive Business Development Services

The aim of our BDS support, coaching and training is to enhance entrepreneurial competencies of business owners, start-ups, and SMEs to enhance employment opportunities. Our BDS package comprises of six components starting from business idea generation and business plan development to access to finance linkage.

Through our digitalized BDS provision, we avail affordable, tailored, and end-to-end business advisory support to young entrepreneurs. Child Safeguards Policy and BDS Guidelines are strictly applicable in our BDS programming.

IBADS4MSEs Programme

Improved Business Advisory and Development Service for MSEs (LI WAY Programme)

Duration: 2 years (Pilot phase until June 2025)
Target: 230 women-owned/led MSEs and startups in Addis Ababa (75% youth)

MENSH Digital Platform

Our innovative digital BDS platform provides accessible business advisory services through public-private partnerships and market system development approaches.

Conflict Response in Tigray Region

In response to the conflict in northern Ethiopia, our partnership with Ethiopian Enterprise Development (EED) and the Ministry of Industry focuses on revitalizing industries and SMEs in Tigray. Our recent two-day training for Tigray Regional State Bureau of Industry officials emphasized key areas like initiative-taking, empathy, and strategic thinking.
